column2: Why predict Diabetes for a 50-year-old female with a BMI of 25 and a Diabetes Pedigree Function of 0.3, rather than a 40-year-old male with a BMI of 22 and a Diabetes Pedigree Function of 0.1?
Predict(Diabetes, Female(BMI = 25, DPF = 0.3), age = 50) and not Predict(Diabetes, Male(BMI = 22, DPF = 0.1), age = 40)
